Package rover

Class Rover

java.lang.Object
rover.Rover
public class Rover
extends java.lang.Object
To carry out a mission, the most common way is to build and use a rover. The Rover class aims at defining everything that a rover is composed of and needs to work properly, e.g. sensors, motors, initializations and so on.
Author:
Antoine Stevan

  • Method Details

    • build

      public static Rover build()
      Default constructor of a Rover. Each component is initialized with a default value. Each component is assigned to a default port on the brick : ultrasonic (4); color (1); pliers (A); right (B); left (C).
      Returns:
      a newly built default rover.

    • build

      public static Rover build​(lejos.hardware.port.Port ultrasonic_port, lejos.hardware.port.Port color_port, lejos.hardware.port.Port pliers_motor_port, lejos.hardware.port.Port right_motor_port, lejos.hardware.port.Port left_motor_port)
      Constructor with parameters for a Rover. User can manually set the ports for his own rover by given a set of ports in the following order : (1) ultrasonic sensor, (2) color sensor, (3) pliers motor, (4) right motor and (5) left motor.
      Parameters:
      ultrasonic_port - the port the ultrasonic sensor should be connected to.
      color_port - the port the color sensor should be connected to.
      pliers_motor_port - the port the pliers motor should be connected to.
      right_motor_port - the port the right motor should be connected to.
      left_motor_port - the port the left motor should be connected to.
      Returns:
      a newly built rover with custom port layout.

    • init_ultrasonic_sensor

      public boolean init_ultrasonic_sensor()
      Initialization of the ulrasonic sensor. Tries to connect the brick and the ultrasonic sensor through the EV3UltrasonicSensor class. If the sensor is not connected, an error is thrown, handled by the method, converted to boolean and returned.
      Returns:
      true if the ultrasonic sensor is properly connected to the right port, false if any error occurs.

    • init_color_sensor

      public boolean init_color_sensor()

      Returns:
      true if the color sensor is properly connected to the right port, false if any error occurs.

    • init_pliers_motor

    • init_peripherals

      public void init_peripherals()
      Initializes all the peripherals that should be connected to the rover. Call every initialization methods through the internal doctor.
